Review the following PR.

## PR Information
- **Title**: Add optional redirect URI to OAuth authorization flow
- **Author**: jeanlaurent
- **Branch**: custom-redirect-url → main
- **Files Changed**: 6

## PR Description
Adds an optional redirect_uri field to GetAuthorizationURLRequest so callers can override the default OAuth callback URL. This allows apps to use custom URI schemes (e.g., myapp://auth/callback) for the OIDC login flow.

### Changes
- proto: Added optional redirect_uri field to GetAuthorizationURLRequest
- auth/oidc: AuthorizationURL() accepts a redirectURI parameter, falls back to configured default when empty
- auth/service: Reads redirect_uri from the request and passes it through
- generated code: Regenerated Go and TypeScript protobuf files

## Diff

Note: Generated protobuf files (auth.pb.go, auth_pb.ts) are omitted — only hand-written code is shown.

